gw.api.domain.account

Interface AccountSyncable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    APDPolicyInvolvedParty, BAPolicyContactRole, BOPPolicyContactRole, CPPolicyContactRole, GLPolicyContactRole, IMPolicyContactRole, PAPolicyContactRole, PlcyNonPriNamedInsured, PolicyAddlInsured, PolicyAddlInterest, PolicyAddlNamedInsured, PolicyAddress, PolicyBillingContact, PolicyContactRole, PolicyDriver, PolicyLaborClient, PolicyLaborContractor, PolicyLocation, PolicyNamedInsured, PolicyOwnerOfficer, PolicyPriNamedInsured, PolicySecNamedInsured, WCLaborContact, WCPolicyContactRole

    public interface AccountSyncable
    Interface for entities that can sync fields with an account-level entity. This interface should be implemented on entities that share data at the account level while also keeping a local copy of the information. An account syncable should be synced to the account when the account syncable is allowed to change and when the account level data is more accurate.

    • Method Detail

      • isSyncedToAccount

        boolean isSyncedToAccount()
        Indicates if the account syncable has its values synced to the account level. An account syncable should be synced to the account when the account syncable is allowed to change and when the account level data is more accurate.

      • getHasChangedPolicyEntityFields

        boolean getHasChangedPolicyEntityFields()

      • getHasMatchingAccountAndPolicyFields

      • assignToSource

        void assignToSource(KeyableBean source)
        Assigns the source to this account syncable, potentially initializing the initial fields. This method should only be called during create or merge.
        Parameters:
        source - The source of this account syncable

      • refreshAccountInformation

        void refreshAccountInformation()
        Refreshes any necessary account information to ensure this account syncable will use the most current data when calling the other methods on this interface.

      • copyPolicyContractData

        void copyPolicyContractData()
        Copies the policy contract data from the account level into the account syncable. Since copying unsynced policy contact data is typically a programming error, this method throws an IllegalStateException if this account syncable is not sycned to the account.

      • copyPolicyContractDataUnchecked

        void copyPolicyContractDataUnchecked()
        Copies the policy contract data from the account level into the account syncable without checking if this account syncable is synced. This method is typically used for initialization where overwriting the policy-level values is not a concern, and it should be used with care.

      • validateAccountAndPolicyEntityFields

        void validateAccountAndPolicyEntityFields()
        Validates that the account and policy entity fields have the same value.
